Reasoning: The paper presents algorithms for reducing the Dueling Bandits problem to the conventional Multi-Armed Bandits problem, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the applicability of the Dueling Bandits problem in learning from implicit user feedback and revealed and stated preferences, which suggests a focus on recommender systems and user modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents theoretical results on regret bounds, which suggests a focus on theoretical computer science, leading to the inclusion of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as likely sub-categories.
